  972782 pter._ Java copysourceimport org.apache.pekko.actor.typed.javadsl.Behaviors;\nThat adds some implicit extension methods that are added to classic and typed ActorSystem, ActorContext and ActorRef in both directions. To convert between typed and classic ActorSystem, ActorContext and ActorRef in both directions there are adapter methods in pekko.actor.typed.javadsl.Adapter. Note the inline comments i
  973836 ic”.","title":"Classic to typed"},{"location":"typed/coexisting.html#typed-to-classic","text":"Let’s turn the example upside down and first start the typed actor and then the classic as a child.\nThe following will show how to create, watch and send messages back and forth from a typed actor to this classic actor:\nScala copysourceobject Classic {\n  def props(): classic.Props = classic.Props(new 
