luster\"},{\"location\":\"cluster-dc.html#classic-multi-dc-cluster\",\"text\":\"This chapter describes h\n4118365 ic actors in the same ActorSystem, see coexistence. For new projects we recommend using the new Actor API.\\nSerialization is the same for Classic and Typed actors. It is described in Serialization, aside from serialization of ActorRef that is described here.\",\"title\":\"Classic Serialization\"},{\"location\":\"serialization-classic.html#dependency\",\"text\":\"To use Serialization, you must add the followin\n4118671 serialization-classic.html#dependency\",\"text\":\"To use Serialization, you must add the following dependency in your project:\\nsbt val PekkoVersion = \\\"2.0.0-M1\\\"\\nlibraryDependencies += \\\"org.apache.pekko\\\" %% \\\"pekko-actor\\\" % PekkoVersion Maven <properties>\\n  <scala.binary.version>2.13</scala.binary.version>\\n</properties>\\n<dependencyManagement>\\n  <dependencies>\\n    <dependency>\\n      <group\n4119033 ncies>\\n    <dependency>\\n      <groupId>org.apache.pekko</groupId>\\n      <artifactId>pekko-bom_${scala.binary.version}</artifactId>\\n      <version>2.0.0-M1</version>\\n      <type>pom</type>\\n      <scope>import</scope>\\n    </dependency>\\n  </dependencies>\\n</dependencyManagement>\\n<dependencies>\\n  <dependency>\\n    <groupId>org.apache.pekko</groupId>\\n    <artifactId>pekko-actor_${scala.binar\n4119489 > Gradle def versions = [\\n  ScalaBinary: \\\"2.13\\\"\\n]\\ndependencies {\\n  implementation platform(\\\"org.apache.pekko:pekko-bom_${versions.ScalaBinary}:2.0.0-M1\\\")\\n\\n  implementation \\\"org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_${versions.ScalaBinary}\\\"\\n}\",\"title\":\"Dependency\"},{\"location\":\"serialization-classic.html#serializing-actorrefs\",\"text\":\"All ActorRefs are serializable when using Serialization with Jac\n4124380 ,\"title\":\"I/O\"},{\"location\":\"io.html#dependency\",\"text\":\"To use I/O, you must add the following dependency in your project:\\nsbt val PekkoVersion = \\\"2