x.html#migration-from-akka-to-apache-pekko\",\"text\":\"These migration notes are designed for users migrating from Akka 2.6 to Pekko 1.0 and assume a basic level of Akka experience. Please feel free to submit an issue or a patch\n4284934 migrate to Akka 2.6 before migrating to Pekko.\",\"title\":\"Migration from Akka to Apache Pekko\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#migration-from-akka-to-apache-pekko\",\"text\":\"These migration notes are designed for users migrating from Akka 2.6 to Pekko 1.0 and assume a basic level of Akka experience. Please feel free to submit an issue or a patch if you feel like the notes can \n4284985 tle\":\"Migration from Akka to Apache Pekko\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#migration-from-akka-to-apache-pekko\",\"text\":\"These migration notes are designed for users migrating from Akka 2.6 to Pekko 1.0 and assume a basic level of Akka experience. Please feel free to submit an issue or a patch if you feel like the notes can be improved.\\nfor Pekko jar dependencies, the group\n4286303 aults to 7355. With Artery Remoting, Akka defaults to 25520, while Pekko defaults to 17355. Cluster Management users should read the pekko-management migration guide\",\"title\":\"Migration from Akka to Apache Pekko\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#dependency-changes\",\"text\":\"The Scala 2.13/Scala 3 versions of Pekko no longer include scala-java8-compat as a dependency. This mea\n4286329  Remoting, Akka defaults to 25520, while Pekko defaults to 17355. Cluster Management users should read the pekko-management migration guide\",\"title\":\"Migration from Akka to Apache Pekko\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#dependency-changes\",\"text\":\"The Scala 2.13/Scala 3 versions of Pekko no longer include scala-java8-compat as a dependency. This means if you were relying on \n4286380 ults to 17355. Cluster Management users should read the pekko-management migration guide\",\"title\":\"Migration from Akka to Apache Pekko\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#dependency-changes\",\"text\":\"The Scala 2.13/Scala 3 versions of Pekko no longer include scala-java8-compat as a dependency. This means if you were relying on scala-java8-compat along with Scala 2.12/Scala 3 as\n4286390 355. Cluster Management users should read the pekko-management migration guide\",\"title\":\"Migration from Akka to Apache Pekko\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#dependency-changes\",\"text\":\"The Scala 2.13/Scala 3 versions of Pekko no longer include scala-java8-compat as a dependency. This means if you were relying on scala-java8-compat along with Scala 2.12/Scala 3 as a transit\n4287613 aded to 2.14.3. reactivestreams is upgraded to 1.0.4. pekko-protobuf-v3 is based on protobuf-java 3.16.3.\",\"title\":\"Dependency Changes\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#miscellaneous-notes\",\"text\":\"Data persisted with “akka-persistence” is usable with “pekko-persistence” and vice versa (Persistence). There is one issue that is fixed in v1.0.3 (related to persisted snapshots \n4287623 14.3. reactivestreams is upgraded to 1.0.4. pekko-protobuf-v3 is based on protobuf-java 3.16.3.\",\"title\":\"Dependency Changes\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-akka-1.0.x.html#miscellaneous-notes\",\"text\":\"Data persisted with “akka-persistence” is usable with “pekko-persistence” and vice versa (Persistence). There is one issue that is fixed in v1.0.3 (related to persisted snapshots - for whic\n4288171 es have experimental support that we would appreciate users to try out in test environments (wiki page).\",\"title\":\"Miscellaneous Notes\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-1.1.x.html\",\"text\":\"\",\"title\":\"Migration from Apache Pekko 1.0.x to 1.1.x\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-1.1.x.html#migration-from-apache-pekko-1-0-x-to-1-1-x\",\"text\