he Pekko 1.1.x is binary backwards compatible with 1.0.x with the ordinary exceptions listed in the Binary Compatibility Rules.\\nThis means that updating an application from Apache Pekko 1.0.x t\n4289028 e new Apache Pekko version in your build.\\nThat said, there are some changes to configuration and behavior that should be considered, so reading this migration guide and testing your application thoroughly is recommended.\",\"title\":\"Migration from Apache Pekko 1.0.x to 1.1.x\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-1.1.x.html#splitwhen-splitafter-behavior-change\",\"text\":\"In Apache Pekko 1.0.x\n4289110 nfiguration and behavior that should be considered, so reading this migration guide and testing your application thoroughly is recommended.\",\"title\":\"Migration from Apache Pekko 1.0.x to 1.1.x\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-1.1.x.html#splitwhen-splitafter-behavior-change\",\"text\":\"In Apache Pekko 1.0.x, the splitWhen/splitAfter stream operators on Source/Flow had an optional Substre\n4289168 ding this migration guide and testing your application thoroughly is recommended.\",\"title\":\"Migration from Apache Pekko 1.0.x to 1.1.x\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-1.1.x.html#splitwhen-splitafter-behavior-change\",\"text\":\"In Apache Pekko 1.0.x, the splitWhen/splitAfter stream operators on Source/Flow had an optional SubstreamCancelStrategy parameter which defaulted to SubstreamCan\n4289178 migration guide and testing your application thoroughly is recommended.\",\"title\":\"Migration from Apache Pekko 1.0.x to 1.1.x\"},{\"location\":\"migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-1.1.x.html#splitwhen-splitafter-behavior-change\",\"text\":\"In Apache Pekko 1.0.x, the splitWhen/splitAfter stream operators on Source/Flow had an optional SubstreamCancelStrategy parameter which defaulted to SubstreamCancelStrateg\n\n\n[Showing lines 50-175 of 175 (50.0KB limit). Full output: /tmp/pi-bash-82c8663535c5db11.log]"}], "details": {"