ko:pekko-cluster-metrics_${versions.ScalaBinary}\\\"\\n}\\nand add the following configuration stanza to your application.conf :\\npekko.extensions = [ \\\"pekko.cluster.metrics.ClusterMetricsExtension\\\" ]\\nPr\n4049383  [ \\\"pekko.cluster.metrics.ClusterMetricsExtension\\\" ]\\nProject Info: Pekko Cluster Metrics (classic) Artifact org.apache.pekko pekko-cluster-metrics 2.0.0-M1 Snapshots are available JDK versions OpenJDK 17 OpenJDK 21 OpenJDK 25 Scala versions 2.13.18, 3.3.7 JPMS module name pekko.cluster.metrics License Apache-2.0 Home page https://pekko.apache.org/ API documentation API (Scaladoc) API (Javadoc) \n4049546 shots are available JDK versions OpenJDK 17 OpenJDK 21 OpenJDK 25 Scala versions 2.13.18, 3.3.7 JPMS module name pekko.cluster.metrics License Apache-2.0 Home page https://pekko.apache.org/ API documentation API (Scaladoc) API (Javadoc) Forums Apache Pekko User mailing list Apache Pekko Dev mailing list apache/pekko discussion Release notes Release Notes Issues Github issues Sources https://github\n4067426 ml#configuration\",\"text\":\"The Cluster metrics extension can be configured with the following properties:\\ncopysource# SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0\\n\\n###############################################\\n# Pekko Cluster Metrics Reference Config File #\\n###############################################\\n\\n# This is the reference config file that contains all the default settings.\\n# Make your edits\n4074072 ributed-data.html#dependency\",\"text\":\"To use Pekko Distributed Data, you must add the following dependency in your project:\\nsbt val PekkoVersion = \\\"2.0.0-M1\\\"\\nlibraryDependencies += \\\"org.apache.pekko\\\" %% \\\"pekko-distributed-data\\\" % PekkoVersion Maven <properties>\\n  <scala.binary.version>2.13</scala.binary.version>\\n</properties>\\n<dependencyManagement>\\n  <dependencies>\\n    <dependency>\\n \n4074445 ncies>\\n    <dependency>\\n      <groupId>org.apache.pekko</groupId>\\n      <artifactId>pekko-b